        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 5:55PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 555 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Charleston, moving northeast at 75 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Altus...                          Charleston...
Denning...                        Etna...
Alix...                           Bloomer...
Watalula...                       Meg...
Peter Pender...                   Branch...
Wiederkehr Village...             Vesta...
Cecil...                          Taft...
Ursula...                         Ozark...
Fort Chaffee...                   Caulksville...

This includes Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 32 and
42.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
